DAVIS, Director General of Railroads, v. KEENAN. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. April 16, 1923.) No. 229. Alexander & Green, of New York City (Clifton P. Williamson, H. S. Ogden, and Edward W. Bourne, all of New York City, of counsel), for plaintiff in error. Edward J. McCrossin, of New York City, for defendant in error.

Before ROGERS, MANTON and MAYER,. Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment' affirmed.
